******
[2] India (Kerala State)
Date: Fri 26 Dec 2014
Source: Kaumudi Global [edited]
http://kaumudiglobal.com/innerpage1.php?newsid=59318


Cholera was confirmed in 2 children undergoing treatment in a children's hospital in the district. The health department has urged the people in the district to remain vigilant against the spread of cholera. The 2 children are under observation in the hospital.

The children confirmed with cholera are from a family in Athirambuzha. The disease was confirmed following tests conducted. The health department noticed the spread of cholera through contaminated water. The disease spreads through water and is spread by bacteria, _Vibrio cholerae_. Disease enters the body through water and food obtained from unhygienic places.

