******
[3] Diarrhea, fatal - Solomon Islands (Malaita Province)
Date: Sat 27 Dec 2014
Source: Solomon Star News [edited]
http://www.solomonstarnews.com/news/national/5321-diarrhea-claim-9-lives-in-east-malaita


Up to 10 people are confirmed dead in east Kwaio, Malaita as a result of a diarrhea outbreak in the area since November 2014. They include 7 children and 3 adults. Enoch Idui, who comes from the area, said he witnessed a 9 month old child who died from diarrhea. He said the nurse in charge at Namolaelae clinic told him the outbreak was due to unhygienic practices by people living in the area.

"People should practice better hygiene other than living carelessly," Mr Idui said. He said in the past weeks, the clinic was packed with diarrhea affected patients.

However, nurse in-charge of the infection control department at Kilu'ufi Hospital Nixon Olofisau said the diarrhea incidents were not an outbreak but a normal occurrence. "From the reports I get, it was not an outbreak," Mr Olofisau said.

[byline: Lucio Sanga]

--
communicated by:
