<promed@promedmail.org>

[Malaita Province (http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaita_Province, https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3055996,39666) is one of the largest provinces of the Solomon Islands. It is named after its largest island, Malaita (also known as "Big Malaita" or "Maramapaina"). Other islands include South Malaita Island (also called "Small Malaita" or "Maramasike"), Sikaiana Island, and Ontong Java Atoll. The provincial capital and largest urban center is Auki, located on Big Malaita. - Mod.LL]

******
[4] Diarrhea, fatal - Sudan (South Darfur State)
Date: Mon 22 Dec 2014
Source: Radio Dabanga [edited]
https://www.dabangasudan.org/en/all-news/article/children-dying-of-fever-in-south-darfur-s-otash-camp


The mortality rate in the Otash camp for the displaced in Nyala locality, South Darfur has risen in the past 2 months, owing to the spread of a disease causing high fever, vomiting, and diarrhea.

"In particular, children suffer from the disease," a resident of the camp reported to Radio Dabanga. "Many died during the past 2 months, as the staff of the camp's health centre are unable to treat all the patients."

He appealed to the health authorities in South Darfur state to accelerate the provision of medicines, and increase the number of health centres in the camp.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[With fever, the chance that cholera is a major player in this outbreak is low. - Mod.LL

